OL,3,C'I feared l'd be burned alive': Asylum
OL,4,Cseeker in hotel attacked by mob
OL,6,F"We had advance warning about a
OL,7,Fprotest. We didn't take it too
OL,8,Fseriously," he said.
OL,10,F"Our staff said we shouldn't leave the
OL,11,Fhotel, close curtains , don't go out -
OL,12,Fso we thought perhaps it is serious.
OL,14,F"We already have been traumatised by
OL,15,Four own country and we thought the UK
OL,16,Fwas a safe country."
OL,18,FSixty-four police officers, three
OL,19,Fpolice horses and a police dog were
OL,20,Finjured during the disorder.
